On Escalation Ticket # 00440882 the new comment has been added: Sanjay Meghani:

@Michael Burrofato @Adam Pawson-Powell @Carlos Mejia @WaitingOnEngineer

Carlos sent me the log files outside this ticket and noticed a couple of errors with an invalid profile name or a missing global options.xml file. Also, they got the service working on 3/27, but they started getting invalid object name error on 4/3, so I am guessing they have changed the default storage profile in the meantime. 

I would make sure the storage profile is configured properly in the NEA.
Restart the webserver service, which should use the default storage profile and create the necessary tables. 

If it is still an issue, please provide the updated logs from "C:Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITSADatabaseLogsWeb" folder.
